<refnamediv>
<refname>npm-search</refname>
<refpurpose>Search for packages</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
<cmdsynopsis>
  <command>npm</command>    <arg choice='plain'><replaceable>search</replaceable></arg>
    <group choice='opt'><arg choice='plain'>-l </arg><arg choice='plain'>--long </arg></group>
    <arg choice='opt'><arg choice='plain'><replaceable>search</replaceable></arg><arg choice='plain' rep='repeat'><replaceable>terms</replaceable></arg></arg>
    <sbr/>
</cmdsynopsis>
<para>aliases: s, se</para>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>Search the registry for packages matching the search terms.</para>

<para>If a term starts with <emphasis remap='B'>/</emphasis>, then it's interpreted as a regular expression.
A trailing <emphasis remap='B'>/</emphasis> will be ignored in this case.  (Note that many regular
expression characters must be escaped or quoted in most shells.)</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id='configuration'><title>CONFIGURATION</title>

<refsect2 id='long'><title>long</title>
  <blockquote remap='RS'>
  <itemizedlist remap='IP+bullet'>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Default: false</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Type: Boolean</para>

    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  </blockquote> <!-- remap='RE' -->

<para>Display full package descriptions and other long text across multiple
lines. When disabled (default) search results are truncated to fit
neatly on a single line. Modules with extremely long names will
fall on multiple lines.</para>
</refsect2>
</refsect1>

